16/05/2006
TRABZON, Turkey -- The trial against a 16-year old Turkish high school student, accused of murdering Roman Catholic priest Andrea Santoro, began at the Trabzon court on Monday (15 May). 
The teen, identified by the initials O.A., is charged with gunning down Santoro outside his church on 5 February. 
Monday's court session was held behind closed doors, with no media present, due to the defendant's age. 
(TurkishPress.com, Focus - 15/05/06)
